FBIS3-20953 "jpest005___94070" JPRS-EST-94-005 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Science & Technology Europe/International Economic Competitiveness 3 March 1994 WEST EUROPE EAST-WEST RELATIONS EU Funds To Help Convert Russian Defense Industry BR2801131394 Didcot INTERFACE EUROPE in English Dec 93 p16 BR2801131394 Didcot INTERFACE EUROPE Language: English Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "EC to Help Convert Former Soviet Defence Industries"] [Text] Funds from the EC's TACIS [Assistance Program to the CIS] programme are to help switch former Soviet defence industries to civilian production. Some Ecu 4.5 million will go to four former Soviet regions: St. Petersburg and Samara (Russia); Kharkov (Ukraine); and Minsk (Belarus). The industries concerned employ about 12 million people, of whom five million work in weapons production. The 30-month project will be run by British Aerospace and the French consultancy Softrade Intergroupe.
